      "content": "PROGRAM",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "a7de6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 3,
      "content": "PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL Students will gain competence in both ancient Greek and Latin and have the opportunity to read literary, philosophical, and historiographical texts in their original form. To satisfy Greek 1 + Greek 2 or Latin 1 + Latin 2, students may enroll in the summer workshops at Berkeley: Greek 15 and Latin 15. Prior Language Experience After matriculating to Berkeley, students who have studied Latin may sign up to take a placement diagnostic to determine the appropriate course to begin the study of Latin at Berkeley. There is no diagnostic for Greek placement. Please consult with the instructor of the Greek course you think is appropriate for your experience. Students who score 5 in AP Latin may be placed out of Elementary Latin and have that requirement waived. After enrolling at UC Berkeley, UCB AGRS R44 (Classics of the Ancient Mediterranean World) may be substituted for either AGRS 10A or AGRS 10B. Prerequisites Students are required to successfully (grade C or higher) complete one Greek or Latin course at UC Berkeley before declaring the major. More Information The Berkeley Catalog and the department website provide more information about major requirements and course information. Advising: Students with questions about transferring into the major in Greek &amp; Latin are encouraged to contact our undergraduate major advisor(UMA): Cassandra Dunn Department Website: https://dagrs.berkeley.edu/ Email: cassandrajj@berkeley.edu Appointments: Schedule an appointment (in-person or remotely).",
      "contentHtml": "<p><strong>PREPARATION FOR TRANSFER AT THE JUNIOR LEVEL</strong></p><p><br></p><p>Students will gain competence in both ancient Greek and Latin and have the opportunity to read literary, philosophical, and historiographical texts in their original form.</p><p><br></p><p>To satisfy Greek 1 + Greek 2 or Latin 1 + Latin 2, students may enroll in the summer workshops at Berkeley: Greek 15 and Latin 15.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Prior Language Experience</strong></p><p>After matriculating to Berkeley, students who have studied Latin may <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdAcDjY_g89LLfTuDPiSstzkj7e5za6-gmid2uRD4j1GsRKpg/viewform?usp=sf_link\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">sign up to take a placement diagnostic </a>to determine the appropriate course to begin the study of Latin at Berkeley. There is no diagnostic for Greek placement. Please consult with the instructor of the Greek course you think is appropriate for your experience.</p><p><br></p><p>Students who score 5 in AP Latin may be placed out of Elementary Latin and have that requirement waived.</p><p><br></p><p>After enrolling at UC Berkeley, UCB AGRS R44 (Classics of the Ancient Mediterranean World) may be substituted for either AGRS 10A or AGRS 10B.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Prerequisites</strong></p><p>Students are required to successfully (grade C or higher) complete one Greek or Latin course at UC Berkeley before declaring the major.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>More Information</strong></p><p>The <a href=\"https://undergraduate.catalog.berkeley.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Berkeley Catalog</a> and the <a href=\"https://dagrs.berkeley.edu/undergraduate/majors-and-minors/the-language-majors/greek-and-latin\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">department website</a> provide more information about major requirements and course information.</p><p><br></p><p><strong>Advising:</strong></p><p>Students with questions about transferring into the major in Greek &amp; Latin are encouraged to contact our undergraduate major advisor(UMA):</p><p>Cassandra Dunn</p><p>Department Website: https://dagrs.berkeley.edu/</p><p>Email: <a href=\"mailto:cassandrajj@berkeley.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">cassandrajj@berkeley.edu</a></p><p>Appointments: <a href=\"https://calendly.com/cassandra-dunn-ug-advisor\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Schedule an appointment (in-person or remotely).</a></p>"
    }
